  "prompt": "What are the penalties for money laundering under federal law?",
  "response": "Under federal law, money laundering can result in significant criminal penalties, including:\n\n1. Prison Sentences\n- Up to 10-20 years in federal prison per offense\n- Potential consecutive sentences for multiple counts\n\n2. Financial Penalties\n- Substantial fines, often up to $500,000 or twice the value of the property involved\n- Potential asset forfeiture\n\n3. Additional Consequences\n- Criminal record\n- Loss of professional licenses\n- Potential deportation for non-citizens\n- Civil penalties\n\nSpecific penalties depend on factors like transaction amount, intent, and prior criminal history. Prosecution typically occurs under statutes like the Bank Secrecy Act and Money Laundering Control Act.",
